snippet.textDisplay: Brady's greatest skill was always his ability to look past dollar signs and see the value of winning. He knew you can be a dynasty or you can be the highest paid, but you can't be both. So many players can't resist the urge to "get there's" while they're hot, often to the detriment of the team. Look at Dak Prescott in Dallas. That team has the talent to win multiple SBs, the pieces are there, and if he was able to think like Brady, this would be an exciting time for Cowboys fans. But he can't. He wants every last cent that he feels he deserves, and as a result they will lose key pieces that they can't afford to keep under contract. They've already lost an all pro CB in Jones, which is a huge loss given they're poor down field D. Getting Cooper under contract is now more of a challenge, and there's still 15 starters from last year that need new deals, and if Dak gets the deal he wants, there will be less then $30Mil left in the cap to get it done. Here's hurting the team in a worse way then his play can make up for. Something that never happened in NE and why it was Tom Bradys mentality and ability to see the big picture, that was his greatest asset.
